he deployment spec comparison to check for annotation changes and add a watch for the CNO-injected CA bundle ConfigMap in the controller. Let me finalize the code now, starting with the annotation comparison logic in the deployment spec modified function. I see the trustmanager uses `maps.Equal` to compare all annotations, but since it relies on Server-Side Apply it only manages its own fields. For the IstioCSR controller using `Update`, comparing all annotations could trigger unnecessary updates if other controllers add annotations to the fetched deployment. The safer approach would be checking only the specific annotation we care about, though the existing code already compares labels the same way. The `UpdateWithRetry` call replaces the entire deployment object, so comparing all pod template annotations is the right approach to detect whether an update is needed. I'll keep it consistent with how labels are already being compared—this is the simplest and most correct way to handle it.\n\nThere's a subtle difference between `maps.Equal` and `reflect.DeepEqual` when dealing with nil versus empty maps, but since the desired labels are always set, this shouldn't be an issue. For annotations though, if the hash is empty, the desired annotations might be nil, so I need to handle that case properly. The cleanest solution is to just check for the specific annotation value directly, which sidesteps all the nil/empty map complications.\n\nWriting helper function...\n\nNow I'm realizing I need to check where `createOrApplyDeployments` is called from—it's used in `install_istiocsr.go` and possibly in tests, so I need to make sure any signature changes don't break those call sites.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":907,"cache_read_input_tokens":82406,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":907,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"pa